# Radar TypeScript Rules

## Stack

- TypeScript strict (`noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, no `any`)
- Next.js 15 App Router
- Path alias: `@/*` → `src/*`

## Layer boundaries

```typescript
// ✅ API route — thin handler
export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const body = schema.parse(await req.json());
  const result = await createSignal(body); // services/
  return NextResponse.json(result, { status: 201 });
}

// ❌ Business logic in route handler
// ❌ Direct DB access from app/api or ai/ or integrations/
```

## Errors

Return `{ error: string, code: string }` — never stack traces to client.

## Tests

- `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts` colocated or in `tests/unit/`
- Test edge cases: empty input, null, unauthorized, max length
